post_text:
September 11, 2020
Hello FUSD athletes, parents, and guardians,
Due to an oversight, the Baseball/Softball season will not be played during Quarter 2 (Q2) of the 2020 season. The FUSD baseball and softball fields will be overseeded during this time and no events will be permitted.
As a result of this, we will offer SOCCER during Quarter 2 (Q2).
SOCCER will begin on October 5th, 2020.
We will keep you informed on Quarter 3 (Q3) and Quarter 4 (Q4) athletic seasons as we make decisions.
We apologies for the inconvenience but look forward to seeing the athletes on the fields again.
If you have any questions, feel free to contact your school site athletic director.

Thank you,

Jeff Cox, M.Ed.
FUSD #1 Director of K12 Athletics/Community Education

FUSD Community, don't forget to register for the PBHS NHS Blood Drive TOMORROW from 2:00-7:00 PM in the small gym (enter & exit from the south side parking lot). The goal is to collect 120 pints of Blood for Vitalant Blood Services of Arizona.
• Everyone that donates will receive free Antibody testing results!
• Everyone that donates will be entered into a raffle to win a car!
• If you already recovered from COVID, we can use your donated plasma to help others who are battling COVID right now.
• Everyone in attendance must wear a face covering.
Sign up by visiting www.bloodhero.com (Sponsor Code: PostonButte) or call 1-877-25-VITAL (258-4825) to schedule your lifesaving appointment.
If you have any questions please contact our NHS advisor Mrs. Kuebler at
tkuebler@fusdaz.or call the front office at 480-474-6100.
Please see attached flier for details and more information about the car giveaway.

post_text: CONGRATULATIONS to the Poston Butte High School Baseball program, who was selected as a recipient of the ABCA Team Academic Excellence Award. This recognition was awarded to 143 high school programs nationally and only 7 high school programs in the state of Arizona. The 2020 Broncos varsity baseball team had a cumulative GPA of 3.66 with 7 individual student athletes earning a 4.0 GPA or better. They can play baseball also, ranked #3 in AZ in the 4A division prior to the Covid shutdown. An altogether great 2020 for Poston Butte Baseball! post_text:
FUSD family,
This afternoon, Governor Ducey made an announcement to delay the start of school until August 17th. The FUSD administration will be meeting tomorrow morning to address this decision and discuss how to proceed. We appreciate your understanding as we navigate through this on-going, fluid situation together. The FUSD administration will review the Return to Learn plan and will once again be put to the task of creating the best possible educational opportunities for your student(s) while keeping their healthy and safety at the forefront of every decision. We ask for your continued patience as we once again face the challenges the COVID-19 pandemic has bestowed upon us all. We will remain transparent and will communicate the updated plan as soon as it has been completed.

FUSD families,
Our task force has been diligently working to come up with reopening plans to be communicated on June 22nd. I remain hopeful that we will be in phase 3 & will be able to be back in our classrooms for those students who are ready to get back to school. The Task Force is also considering those students who want to attend school virtually. I am confident the Task Force will develop an action plan that will be beneficial to all FUSD students, staff & families. We will figure all of this out because we have great teachers and leaders in FUSD.

On a positive note, this past weekend we had a track meet at Poston Butte High School. 500 track and field athletes descended on San Tan Valley from 22 states across the country. It was awesome! https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_ciFOJvsMkU

Chris Knutsen, Superintendent

Just a reminder to all parents & guardians to please fill out the survey at your ealiest convenience. This will help us better prepare for the future. Thank you for your time.

Dear Parents / Guardians,

FUSD appreciates all you have done in the past couple of months to ensure that students had an opportunity to continue learning during these unprecedented times. Your continued partnership with the schools, teachers and staff, as well as your efforts to guide your student through the learning process has been incredibly valuable.

In our efforts to stay connected, FUSD has provided distance learning with the Flexible Learning Framework. As we look ahead, we hope to improve what we are doing as a school district and to better prepare for the future. Therefore, please take a moment and provide us with your valuable feedback so we can better serve the educational needs of our students and families.

https://forms.gle/KyZVDMjmz7KXBoLj6

Thank you again,

Chris Knutsen
Superintendent

post_text:
VINTAGE WARBIRD FLYOVER!
Approx 9:25 a.m. today, San Tan Valley folks will see a formation of three large, vintage warbirds. The flyover is to commemorate the 75th anniversary of the Victory in Europe. Along the way, these aircraft will also fly over Mesa Cemetery (U.S. and British are buried there), the USS Arizona Monument, and the National Cemetery, just to name a few.

One of the planes may be a B-25 Mitchell (named after Gen. Billy Mitchell) & a B-17 Flying Fortress.

Look for these aircraft flying in to STV from the northeast (from Gold Canyon) around 9:21 a.m. Looks they will be turning north after flying over the Golf Club at Johnson Ranch at 9:26 a.m. From there they will head to Apache Junction at 9:31 a.m. Looking at the flight path, STV will have the longest viewing time since they are turning over Johnson Ranch and will head north just slightly west of their incoming flight direction. All times are approximate. Enjoy the view!

post_text: The FUSD "Feature Teacher" is Sarah McKinney from Mountain Vista Academy. Earlier this year, she was excited to share the installation of a therapy garden that was made possible by a grant from Future Forward Foundation. On a cool fall day, students, teachers & even Supervisor Goodman all got their hands dirty to plant vegetables. Even though our schools have been closed, Sarah McKinney has continued to cultivate the garden so it's ready for when our students return. Her dedication is what FUSD is all about. Thank you Sarah McKinney for all your hard work! #FUSDachieves #closednotclosed #stayconnected Mike Goodman Pinal County Supervisor District 2 Arizona Education News Steve Irvin-ABC15

post_text: Thank you, Mayor Walter for sharing a story as the Town of Florence celebrates The Week of the Young Child. This is an annual celebration hosted by the National Association of the Education of Young Children (NAEYC) to spotlight early learning, young children, their teachers, families, and communities. #FUSDachieves #stayconnected #closednotclosed
shared_text:
Mayor Tara Walter
April 13 at 3:23 PM ·

The Week of the Young Child is an annual celebration hosted by the national Association of the Education of Young Children (NAEYC) to spotlight early learning, young children, their teachers, families, and communities. Spreading the word about the importance of high-quality early learning, the the critical role early childhood educators play in a child's development and learning is critical.
Ms. Michelle Reimer, MA, Community Outreach Coordinator for First Things First, has requested the Town show its support by proclaiming April 11-17, 2020 as Week of the Young Child and acknowledge the importance of education for our children in our community. I hope you enjoy this story, "The Fire Cat" by: Esther Averill, read by Mayor Tara Walter.

Complete the Census online at www.2020census.gov or call toll free 844-330-2020. Everyone in Florence counts!

post_text:
You COUNT in the 2020 Census!
Did you know that being counted impacts the federal funds that communities receive for special education, classroom technology, teacher training, after-school programs, school lunch assistance, and more!
Every household should have received an invitation to participate in the Census. Be sure to respond to the Census and remember to count every person in your home. You can respond to the Census online or by using your mobile device, by phone, or by mail.
Responses to the Census are safe, secure, and protected by federal law. Your answers can only be used to produce statistics, and cannot be used by any government agency or court including the FBI, CIA, DHS, and ICE. The only questions asked are simple questions like age, gender, and the number of people living in your home, including children. Be counted and help shape the future of Arizona! www.fusdaz.com
https://www.2020census.gov/

2020CENSUS.GOV
2020 Census | United States Census Bureau

post_text:
FUSD has some pretty amazing teachers on staff! Even though we are learning online, they are still able to make those meaningful connections with our students. We want to recognize their efforts so today's FUSD FEATURE TEACHER is: Cheryl Callahan from Copper Basin K-8. Cheryl shared,

"I have been doing a Bedtime Story at 8:00 pm every night since Wednesday, March 25, 2020. The kids LOVE seeing each other using MEET! I have been recording the stories since the second night and posting in out GC. I have chatted with parents before reading the story. the kids have chatted with each other before and after our story. They have even started using the chat to communicate with each other as well. It's been fun! I have told them that I will do this every night (weekends too) until we go back to school - or the end of what should have been school this year."

Today FUSD will implement the Flexible Learning Framework. Take a moment to breathe as we navigate this uncharted territory together. We have added a Flexible Learning Toolkit resource page on the FUSD website at https://www.fusdaz.com/Page/2111

Parents can email our help desk at
Classroom-help@fusdaz.org or call our parent helpline at 520-723-6475 and 480-987-5394. This helpline is for Google Classroom or Google Meet assistance only at this time.

FUSD appreciates our amazing Tech Team who are working hard to ensure a smooth transition into the online learning environment. FUSD is committed to our students & will stay connected with them in order to provide some normalcy & structure. Teaching, learning, and our community – although done remotely - will continue. #stayconnected #FUSDachieves #closednotclosed

Congratulations to Quest Williams on being named the Boys Basketball Player of the Year in the 4A Desert Sky Region! That's not all; the accolades keep coming.
“Quest is a very talented player who had the best year of anyone in the Desert Sky Region. He led us in most statistical categories and was one of the main reasons why we were able to make it back to the state tournament this season. “
-Poston Butte Head Basketball Coach Mike Christenson https://www.pinalcentral.com/casa_grande_dispatch/local_sports/bronco-s-williams-leads-boys-basketball-all-county-team/article_84f1ae88-18f9-5c4f-a942-a44e8eec6538.html
